<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/48105248-kayla-fraser"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1584560089i/48105248._UX100_CR0,18,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/48105248-kayla-fraser">Kayla Fraser</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I read this book with Gr. 8&apos;s, although I did it as a read aloud. This way I could filter some of the language and discuss the sexual abuse in an auth<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I read this book with Gr. 8's, although I did it as a read aloud. This way I could filter some of the language and discuss the sexual abuse in an authentic way. I did it as part of a unit in LA where we studied the concept of adversity and I thought it was a perfect book to enhance the topic! It also helps students become aware of the direct and generational effects of residential schools in Canada. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
