        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1187640205" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12866072275172981229">Saul Indian Horse is but eight years old when he is literally yanked from the arms of his grandmother and carted off to a church-run residential school. Racism is rampant, abuse out of control. Punishment is dire for any child foolish enough to run away, many were punished, some disappeared, others died. As he tries to make his way, an unexpected introduction to ice hockey ends up being the saving grace for Saul. <br/><br/>The writing is clean and simple, it reads very quickly, and tells a tale both heart</span>
  <span id="freeText12866072275172981229" style="display:none">Saul Indian Horse is but eight years old when he is literally yanked from the arms of his grandmother and carted off to a church-run residential school. Racism is rampant, abuse out of control. Punishment is dire for any child foolish enough to run away, many were punished, some disappeared, others died. As he tries to make his way, an unexpected introduction to ice hockey ends up being the saving grace for Saul. <br /><br />The writing is clean and simple, it reads very quickly, and tells a tale both heartbreaking and uplifting. Listen to Saul tell his story as he works to find peace in his heart for the harsh realities that life has dealt him. You will root for him to find his way home. Home - where memories are held, things kept, the sum of us. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12866072275172981229" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
